Description:
You can use CSS gradients to create smooth color transitions. The background or background-image property can be set to a linear or radial gradient.

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Inline Gradient Property</title>
  <style>
    .gradient-box {
      width: 300px;
      height: 150px;
      background: linear-gradient(90deg, #ff9a9e, #fad0c4);
      border: 2px solid #ff6f91;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      font-weight: bold;
      color: #333;
      margin-top: 20px;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <h2>16. Inline Gradient Property</h2>

  <div class="gradient-box">
    Linear Gradient Background
  </div>

</body>
</html>
